Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Toss @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @turkish spice blend{1/2%tsp}. Roast until tender and lightly browned, about ~{25%minutes}.

Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}.

Bring water and a large pinch of salt to a boil in a large #pot{}. Once water is boiling, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce}. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large #ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and scallion whites. Cook until softened, about ~{3-5%minutes}. Add @turkish spice blend{1/2%tsp} and cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.

Whisk @flour{1%tablespoon} into pan and cook until golden, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Slowly pour @milk{1%box} into pan while whisking to combine. Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and bring to a simmer. Let bubble until thickened, about ~{2%minutes}. Remove from heat and add @Italian cheese blend{1%cup}, stirring until cheese is melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add cooked pasta and cauliflower to cheese sauce and stir to combine. Bake in oven until top is lightly crisped, about ~{5%minutes}. In a large #bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{3%ounce} with @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon} and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Serve on the side.

> TIP: Transfer mixture to baking dish if you don't have an ovenproof pan.

> If the bright orange mac is an occasional treat, this is one you can enjoy any night of the week.